LIKE without wildcard uses an exact point range, same as equality
Condition: (value in [\'example.com\', \'example.com\'])
Condition: (value in [\'example.com\', \'example.com\'])
NOT LIKE without wildcard excludes an exact point range, same as inequality
Condition: (value not in [\'example.com\', \'example.com\'])
Condition: (value not in [\'example.com\', \'example.com\'])
An escaped wildcard is a literal, so the pattern is still an exact match
Condition: (value in [\'example.com%\', \'example.com%\'])
A pattern with a real wildcard still uses the half-open prefix range
Condition: (value in [\'example.com\', \'example.con\'))
Results stay correct: exact LIKE matches equality, NOT LIKE matches inequality
